                <h1>Understanding Background Image Repeat in CSS</h1>
                <p>Background image repeat refers to the CSS property that controls how a background image is displayed in a web element. By setting the "background-repeat" property, you can specify whether the image should repeat vertically or horizontally, or not at all. This allows for flexible design choices, ensuring a seamless and visually appealing layout.</p>
